OL,5,Cshoppers
OL,7,F"Looking at March and April together
OL,8,Fhowever, the overall picture for the
OL,9,FUK is more balanced, with footfall
OL,10,Facross the two months up just 0.2%
OL,11,Fyear-on-year.
OL,13,F"While this suggests that April's
OL,14,Fgains largely offset March's dip, it
OL,15,Falso highlights the importance of
OL,16,Fsustained engagement beyond seasonal
OL,17,Fpeaks. Retailers will now be looking
OL,18,Fto build on this momentum as we move
OL,19,Finto the summer months."
